Troll the ancient Yuletide carol

8
00:00:48,210 --> 00:00:52,050
Fa-la-la-la-la
La-la-la-la

9
00:00:52,130 --> 00:00:54,220
Whoa!

10
00:00:56,390 --> 00:00:59,390
Deck the halls
with boughs of holly

11
00:00:59,470 --> 00:01:02,350
Ha-ha. There must be much,
much more holly.

12
00:01:02,430 --> 00:01:04,430
'Tis the season to be...

13
00:01:04,520 --> 00:01:05,850
What's this? There's too much holly.

14
00:01:05,940 --> 00:01:08,400
Whoa! Slow down, lad.

15
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:11,440
Don we now our gay apparel

16
00:01:11,530 --> 00:01:14,150
No, no, no, no more mistletoe.

17
00:01:18,780 --> 00:01:21,580
Chip, away from
those presents, dear.

18
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:26,080
Mama, I found one for me!

19
00:01:26,170 --> 00:01:28,040
Can I open it, Mama? Can I?

20
00:01:28,130 --> 00:01:31,340
-Well, just one.
-Oh, boy!

21
00:01:31,630 --> 00:01:33,630
It's good to see the boy
having a proper Christmas.

22
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:36,840
Not like last year.

23
00:01:37,010 --> 00:01:40,340
Yes.
This is much more agreeable.

24
00:01:40,430 --> 00:01:43,260
Well, I thought last year
was quite nice.

25
00:01:43,350 --> 00:01:47,600
Yes, well, I suppose I...
I did manage to save Christmas.

26
00:01:47,690 --> 00:01:50,060
-You?
-Yes, me.

27
00:01:51,230 --> 00:01:53,520
If not for my skillful
and decisive leadership,

28
00:01:53,610 --> 00:01:54,820
all would've been lost.

29
00:01:54,900 --> 00:01:58,740
Leadership? Ha!
You could not lead a horse to water.

30
00:01:58,820 --> 00:02:00,200
What are you yammering about?

31
00:02:01,410 --> 00:02:02,620
It was all my idea.

32
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:05,620
Your idea?
Everyone knows it was mine.

33
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:10,120
Heavens. How many times are
we going to have to go over this story?

34
00:02:10,210 --> 00:02:14,550
-Story?
-Until someone gets his facts straight.

35
00:02:14,630 --> 00:02:17,470
-Why don't you tell it, Mama?
-Capital idea.

36
00:02:17,550 --> 00:02:19,680
Well, I don't know.

37
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:21,300
Come now, Mrs. Potts.

38
00:02:21,390 --> 00:02:24,350
Surely you recall
how I saved Christmas.

39
00:02:25,350 --> 00:02:26,600
Tut-tut-tut-tut. No leading the witness.

40
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:29,140
Please, Mama, tell the story.

41
00:02:29,230 --> 00:02:31,480
Oh, all right.

42
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:35,610
Ah! Now we will hear
what really happened.

43
00:02:35,690 --> 00:02:37,780
Well, let's see.

44
00:02:37,860 --> 00:02:40,950
Belle, terrified by the master's anger,

45
00:02:41,030 --> 00:02:42,660
ran away from the castle

46
00:02:42,740 --> 00:02:46,330
straight into a pack of wolves.

47
00:02:46,410 --> 00:02:49,000
But the master saved her.

48
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:51,040
They began to be friends.

49
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:52,420
Ah-ah-ah.

50
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:54,920
That's where l came in.

51
00:02:56,420 --> 00:02:59,510
Where could he be?
Goodness knows.

52
00:02:59,590 --> 00:03:02,130
We've searched every last corner.

53
00:03:02,220 --> 00:03:05,720
I'm beginning to think
he's not in the castle at all.

54
00:03:07,850 --> 00:03:10,060
Voilà! There he is!

55
00:03:10,140 --> 00:03:12,940
-Wonderful!
-No time to waste.

56
00:03:13,020 --> 00:03:14,900
We must find a way
to get them together.

57
00:03:14,980 --> 00:03:17,820
Let's go! Love will not wait.

58
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:21,280
You really think she's the one?
Will she break the spell?

59
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:23,870
I knew it from the moment
I set eyes on her.

60
00:03:23,950 --> 00:03:28,490
If anyone can reach the master,
Belle can. Such a kind soul.

61
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:30,330
And her looks
don't hurt either.

62
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:33,290
Wait for me!

63
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:44,510
-Hi, Belle.
-Oh, hello.

64
00:03:45,050 --> 00:03:47,310
Chip, do you know what day it is?

65
00:03:47,390 --> 00:03:50,930
Well, it's not Tuesday...

66
00:03:51,020 --> 00:03:54,730
No, silly. Today is December 24th.

67
00:03:54,810 --> 00:03:58,980
-The day before Christmas.
-And what a beautiful day it is.

68
00:03:59,070 --> 00:04:01,860
A wonderful day for a morning stroll.

69
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:05,990
Yes, yes. Nothing starts the day
like a brisk walk around the grounds.

70
00:04:06,070 --> 00:04:08,620
Yeah!
Or you could go ice-skating.

71
00:04:08,700 --> 00:04:11,000
-Ha-ha. Wahoo!
-Yes, fresh air, exercise. Ha-ha.

72
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:13,540
-In moderation, of course.

73
00:04:14,710 --> 00:04:17,420
Come along, Belle, dear.
The great outdoors awaits.

74
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,460
Yeah, let's go!

75
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:30,260
Oh. Good morning.

76
00:04:30,350 --> 00:04:33,560
Huh? Whoa...

77
00:04:34,850 --> 00:04:37,520
Oh, dear. Are you all right?

78
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:40,400
Uh... Uh...

79
00:04:42,150 --> 00:04:47,280
I fell and I landed on my...
On... On the ice.

80
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:49,370
It's pretty slippery.

81
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:52,620
Yes, it's slippery.

82
00:04:53,540 --> 00:04:56,040
This is a perfect day for skating.

83
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:59,090
Come on.

84
00:04:59,710 --> 00:05:00,960
Hmm?

85
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:03,510
Come on.

86
00:05:03,590 --> 00:05:04,970
No.

87
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:11,100
-Go on, Master. It might be fun.
-Go for it!

88
00:05:11,180 --> 00:05:13,140
Hmm. Hmm?

89
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:17,230
Come on!
Not so fast.

90
00:05:17,850 --> 00:05:18,900
Ooo-ooo la-la.

91
00:05:20,070 --> 00:05:22,900
Come on. Why don't you try it like this?

92
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:27,740
One, two, three. One, two, three.
See? It's easy.

93
00:05:29,570 --> 00:05:35,370
One, two, three.

94
00:05:35,580 --> 00:05:36,620
Ho-ho-ho.

95
00:05:36,710 --> 00:05:39,290
Yes, I think this may work.

96
00:06:03,570 --> 00:06:07,190
Bravo! Bravo! Encore!

97
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:12,030
Fife, you approve?

98
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:15,080
Oh, Maestro, it's magnificent!

99
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:18,410
Oh, come along. It's merely an opera

100
00:06:20,710 --> 00:06:24,550
to bring the house down.

101
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,130
-Ooh!

102
00:06:27,170 --> 00:06:29,720
Is there a part for a piccolo?

103
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:31,760
Absolutely.

104
00:06:37,930 --> 00:06:41,520
Solo for Fife in B-flat.

105
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:45,650
-Ooh. I'd do anything for a solo.
-Yes.

106
00:06:46,650 --> 00:06:50,110
I know. Now, Fifey,

107
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:52,360
in the midst of my crescendo,

108
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:56,040
I thought I heard merriment
outside the window.

109
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:58,580
Have a little look-see, will you?

110
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:03,750
Wow! Would you look at that?

111
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:07,550
Well, I think I might.
I'll just pick myself up and...

112
00:07:07,630 --> 00:07:08,630
Oh!

113
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:11,340
What's this? Heavens, look.

114
00:07:11,430 --> 00:07:13,930
I'm bolted to the wall!

115
00:07:14,010 --> 00:07:15,810
Oh, right.

116
00:07:17,470 --> 00:07:20,430
Um, the master is skating.

117
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:24,110
Skating? Why on earth
would he do a thing like that?

118
00:07:24,190 --> 00:07:27,270
Probably because that
pretty girl is holding his hand.

119
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:29,820
-What? Belle?
-Hey.

120
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:34,160
Maybe if she falls in love with him,
the spell will be broken,

121
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:36,410
and we'll be human again!

122
00:07:38,370 --> 00:07:40,290
Trust me, Fife.

123
00:07:40,370 --> 00:07:43,870
-Humanity is entirely overrated.

124
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:46,790
Before the enchantment,
there was no need

125
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:50,550
for my particular brand of genius.

126
00:07:51,050 --> 00:07:54,300
But now the master needs my melodies

127
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:57,140
to feed his tormented soul.

128
00:07:57,720 --> 00:08:00,270
I am his confidant

129
00:08:00,890 --> 00:08:02,890
and his best friend.

130
00:08:03,770 --> 00:08:07,650
And I won't let some peasant girl
ruin it for me!

131
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:13,150
Fife, see to it that this blossoming love

132
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:15,530
withers on the vine.

133
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:19,080
Yes, Maestro Forte.

134
00:08:19,410 --> 00:08:21,540
One, two, three.

135
00:08:21,620 --> 00:08:24,750
One, two, three. One, two, three.
One, two, three.

136
00:08:24,830 --> 00:08:26,750
I think I've got it!

137
00:08:32,510 --> 00:08:34,760
Hey, down in front. I wanna see.

138
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:37,260
Let me see. I wanna see, too!

139
00:08:38,510 --> 00:08:39,600
Shh!

140
00:08:40,970 --> 00:08:44,190
Quiet. Oh, this is very promising.

141
00:08:44,270 --> 00:08:46,770
Ah, yes, there is something in the air.

142
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:49,150
-Could it be love?

143
00:08:49,230 --> 00:08:51,190
Love? Oh, oh, oh, ooh.

144
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:52,940
Uh. Oh. Oh.

145
00:08:53,030 --> 00:08:54,650
I've got to stop them.

146
00:08:54,740 --> 00:08:55,740
Oh!

147
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:00,530
Help!

148
00:09:00,950 --> 00:09:03,620
Whoa-oh-oh-oh!

149
00:09:03,870 --> 00:09:06,040
What's that little toot up to?

150
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:07,630
Whoa!

151
00:09:13,340 --> 00:09:15,380
Mmm-mmm.

152
00:09:17,470 --> 00:09:19,550
Stop!

153
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:40,530
It's a Christmas angel, see?

154
00:09:42,700 --> 00:09:43,910
Oh.

155
00:09:46,330 --> 00:09:48,370
This is no angel.

156
00:09:48,830 --> 00:09:51,670
It's the shadow of a monster.

157
00:09:59,430 --> 00:10:02,680
Oh, Forte is going to be so proud of me.

158
00:10:06,980 --> 00:10:09,270
I don't know why I bother.

159
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:13,110
Now he's worse than ever.

160
00:10:13,610 --> 00:10:15,860
Don't lose heart, dearest.

161
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:33,840
I hate Christmas.

162
00:10:43,050 --> 00:10:45,720
The music helps?

163
00:10:45,810 --> 00:10:50,020
Your music is the only thing
that helps me forget.

164
00:10:50,100 --> 00:10:52,650
Don't worry, old friend.

165
00:10:52,730 --> 00:10:55,020
I'm here for you,

166
00:10:55,110 --> 00:10:57,440
just as I have been,

167
00:10:57,530 --> 00:11:00,240
just as I always will be.

168
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:03,990
Why is the beast such a grump?

169
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:06,660
I don't know. He's always like that.

170
00:11:07,410 --> 00:11:09,750
-Even at Christmas?
-Yep.

171
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:13,330
Belle, what's Christmas?

172
00:11:13,420 --> 00:11:15,840
Oh, Chip, you must know
about Christmas.

173
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:19,340
Stockings in front of the fire? Tree?

174
00:11:19,420 --> 00:11:21,800
Tinsel? Presents?

175
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:23,930
Presents? Do I get one?

176
00:11:24,550 --> 00:11:27,510
Of course. Everyone gets
a present on Christmas.

177
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:31,020
-Oh, even the master?
-Yes, even the master.

178
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:34,360
-What are you gonna get him?
-I don't really know him well enough

179
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:36,520
to know what he would want.

180
00:11:36,610 --> 00:11:40,820
-What would you want?
-Well, what I love most

181
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:44,620
in the world are my books, my stories.

182
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:47,200
Why don't you get the master a story?

183
00:11:47,290 --> 00:11:50,620
You're right, Chip. A story.

184
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:55,960
When l get to know him

185
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:59,420
We'll find more things to say

186
00:11:59,510 --> 00:12:02,550
One day I wiII reach him

187
00:12:02,630 --> 00:12:06,050
There has to be a way

188
00:12:06,140 --> 00:12:09,010
Everyone needs someone

189
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:12,430
He must need someone, too

190
00:12:12,520 --> 00:12:15,770
When l get to know him better

191
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:19,400
Here's what l will do

192
00:12:20,570 --> 00:12:23,360
l'll read him stories

193
00:12:23,450 --> 00:12:26,820
From picture books
all filled with wonder

194
00:12:26,910 --> 00:12:29,870
Magic worlds where the impossible

195
00:12:29,950 --> 00:12:33,120
Becomes the everyday

196
00:12:33,210 --> 00:12:36,380
We'll find a mountaintop

197
00:12:36,460 --> 00:12:39,590
And some moonbeams to sit under

198
00:12:39,670 --> 00:12:45,880
l'll lead because l know the way

199
00:12:45,970 --> 00:12:49,100
So much to discover

200
00:12:49,180 --> 00:12:52,470
l do it all the time

201
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:55,600
l could live inside bright pages

202
00:12:55,690 --> 00:12:58,650
Where the words all rhyme

203
00:12:58,730 --> 00:13:01,480
We will slay the dragons

204
00:13:01,570 --> 00:13:03,650
That still follow him around

205
00:13:04,860 --> 00:13:08,280
And he'll smile
Yes, he'll smile

206
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:11,540
As his dreams leave the ground

207
00:13:11,620 --> 00:13:14,500
Stories and stories

208
00:13:14,580 --> 00:13:18,040
About mermaids, kings
and sunken treasure

209
00:13:18,130 --> 00:13:21,170
Magic worlds where the impossible

210
00:13:21,250 --> 00:13:24,720
Becomes the everyday

211
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:27,970
l know a tiny place

212
00:13:28,050 --> 00:13:31,310
Just a dot too small to measure

213
00:13:31,390 --> 00:13:33,350
l'll take him there

214
00:13:33,430 --> 00:13:37,640
l know the way

215
00:13:37,730 --> 00:13:40,900
Stories about heroes

216
00:13:40,980 --> 00:13:44,650
Who overcame their deepest sorrow

217
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:47,780
They'll put hope into his heart again

218
00:13:47,860 --> 00:13:51,280
He'll cherish every day

219
00:13:51,370 --> 00:13:54,660
He'll find a better world

220
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:58,080
And the strength to face tomorrow

221
00:13:58,170 --> 00:14:04,170
l'm sure that
when he knows the way

222
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:06,470
He'll want

223
00:14:06,550 --> 00:14:12,930
To stay

224
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:21,860
Do you think the master
will like his gift?

225
00:14:21,940 --> 00:14:23,020
I do.

226
00:14:23,110 --> 00:14:25,730
So does this mean
we're gonna have a Christmas?

227
00:14:25,820 --> 00:14:28,150
Uh-huh. Absolutely.

228
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:30,490
Absolutely not.

229
00:14:30,570 --> 00:14:32,530
Why not?

230
00:14:32,620 --> 00:14:36,870
Out of the question. Not a chance.
Dream on. An impossibility. Forget it.

231
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:40,670
Come on!

232
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:42,170
-Suck in that gut.

233
00:14:42,250 --> 00:14:46,460
-Mon ami. Get with the spirit. Unwind.

234
00:14:46,550 --> 00:14:49,510
-Oh, dear.
-Come on, love. Have a heart.

235
00:14:49,590 --> 00:14:52,890
Yeah. Come on.

236
00:14:52,970 --> 00:14:57,310
-No, no, and... Let me think...
-Uh-huh? Uh-huh?

237
00:14:57,390 --> 00:14:58,980
-No!

238
00:14:59,060 --> 00:15:01,850
This is where I put my foot down.

239
00:15:02,230 --> 00:15:04,360
Wait. Get out of...

240
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:08,280
The master has forbidden Christmas!

241
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:09,740
-Oh, dear.

242
00:15:09,820 --> 00:15:11,570
Forbid Christmas?

243
00:15:11,660 --> 00:15:13,910
No one can forbid Christmas.

244
00:15:13,990 --> 00:15:16,160
He doesn't wish
to be reminded of his past,

245
00:15:16,240 --> 00:15:19,830
and Christmas is
a most painful reminder of it.

246
00:15:19,910 --> 00:15:22,750
I, for one, do not wish to torture him.

247
00:15:22,830 --> 00:15:26,090
I, for one, think a little Christmas
cheer would do him some good.

248
00:15:26,170 --> 00:15:27,800
-Yeah.
-Oh? Hmm.

249
00:15:28,340 --> 00:15:32,260
The girl is right.
It is up to us to do something.

250
00:15:32,340 --> 00:15:35,510
Gosh! It's not our place
to get involved.

251
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:39,600
No, no, no, no! We just can't
mind our own beeswax, can we?

252
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:43,560
Just have to stick our wick
where it doesn't belong.

253
00:15:47,610 --> 00:15:48,860
Whoa!

254
00:15:55,740 --> 00:15:58,910
-Oh, humiliating.
-Pish posh.

255
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,160
I think it's a wonderful idea.

256
00:16:01,250 --> 00:16:05,750
But the master doesn't want it.
His castle, his rules.

257
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:07,790
It's not fair.

258
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:11,970
He's right. It's not fair!

259
00:16:12,050 --> 00:16:14,430
Don't whine, glasses.

260
00:16:14,510 --> 00:16:17,050
Sorry.

261
00:16:17,140 --> 00:16:20,600
Look at us,
squabbling and bickering.

262
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:23,310
Breaks my heart to see it, it does.

263
00:16:23,390 --> 00:16:26,310
And we used to be at our very best
at Christmas.

264
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:30,650
Why, we used to prepare
a feast for the entire castle.

265
00:16:30,740 --> 00:16:34,070
Ah! You could have
some stuffed turkey.

266
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:36,780
-Cranberry sauce.
-Shortbread cookies.

267
00:16:36,870 --> 00:16:38,910
Mince pies.
Potatoes.

268
00:16:38,990 --> 00:16:41,160
-Gravy.
-And Christmas pudding!

269
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:44,710
Uh, pudding? With... With custard?

270
00:16:44,790 --> 00:16:49,000
