Of course with custard.

271
00:16:49,090 --> 00:16:51,760
-And raisins and brandy,

272
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:54,420
-and all those things you like.

273
00:16:55,260 --> 00:16:57,590
Ohh. Oh, I...

274
00:16:59,390 --> 00:17:01,970
-All right.
-Yes!

275
00:17:02,060 --> 00:17:05,390
But if the master finds out about this,
he will be furious,

276
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:08,360
so, everybody, keep quiet.

277
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:11,480
Come on!
What are we waiting for, Christmas?

278
00:17:11,570 --> 00:17:14,110
Good heavens, we don't have
much time. It's Christmas Eve!

279
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,820
-I'll see to the dinner.
-I'll get some mistletoe.

280
00:17:17,990 --> 00:17:19,870
We need to brighten this place up.

281
00:17:19,950 --> 00:17:22,240
Belle, I know someone who will help.

282
00:17:22,330 --> 00:17:26,250
Now, now, wait for me.
I'm in charge here. I'm in charge.

283
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:29,960
Wait for me!

284
00:17:31,340 --> 00:17:34,760
One-thousand one,
one-thousand two,

285
00:17:34,840 --> 00:17:36,720
one-thousand three...

286
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:40,300
-Are we there yet?
-Not yet.

287
00:17:40,390 --> 00:17:43,470
Oh, boy, there sure
are a lot of stairs here.

288
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:46,350
One-thousand seven,
one-thousand eight,

289
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:49,060
one-thousand nine, one-thousand ten...

290
00:17:57,780 --> 00:18:01,200
Hello?

291
00:18:03,490 --> 00:18:05,750
Do not be afraid, mes amis.

292
00:18:05,830 --> 00:18:10,000
It is I, Lumiere.
We have come to pay you a little visit.

293
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:17,590
-Lumiere?
-Angelique.

294
00:18:18,180 --> 00:18:21,470
-Ah, Lumiere, finally.

295
00:18:21,550 --> 00:18:24,850
I thought we were to be locked away
in this dusty attic forever.

296
00:18:24,970 --> 00:18:27,680
Ah, Angelique, mon amour.

297
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:33,270
Your eyes are still so lovely
after all these years.

298
00:18:33,360 --> 00:18:35,280
Lumiere, please!

299
00:18:35,360 --> 00:18:37,650
You'll tarnish the halo.

300
00:18:38,860 --> 00:18:42,160
Oh, yes. This is Belle, our guest.

301
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:46,040
-Pleased to meet you.
-And this is Angelique.

302
00:18:46,120 --> 00:18:48,080
She is the castle decorator.

303
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:50,790
You mean was the castle decorator.

304
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:54,460
I am not responsible
for this baroque atrocity.

305
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:56,590
When I was in charge,

306
00:18:56,670 --> 00:19:00,590
the castle was full of light and beauty.

307
00:19:00,680 --> 00:19:03,850
But, chérie,
that is why we have come.

308
00:19:03,930 --> 00:19:06,560
Gather around, mes enfants.

309
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:09,350
-We are planning the greatest

310
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:12,480
Christmas celebration ever.

311
00:19:20,820 --> 00:19:22,660
No, stop!

312
00:19:22,740 --> 00:19:24,830
-What is it, chérie?

313
00:19:24,910 --> 00:19:27,040
Why do you raise my hopes...

314
00:19:27,120 --> 00:19:31,830
I... I mean, their hopes...
Only to have them dashed?

315
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:34,080
Well, no more.

316
00:19:35,550 --> 00:19:37,050
But it's Christmas Eve.

317
00:19:37,130 --> 00:19:40,090
Without you, we'll never get
the castle decorated in time.

318
00:19:40,170 --> 00:19:44,760
Ha! Christmas? Hmph!
I refuse to hope for it anymore.

319
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:46,970
I will not be disappointed again.

320
00:19:47,060 --> 00:19:50,140
But this is to be
the greatest celebration ever.

321
00:19:50,230 --> 00:19:52,350
We cannot do it without you.

322
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:56,060
Well, but of course you cannot.

323
00:19:56,150 --> 00:19:59,110
Christmas takes planning
and organization.

324
00:19:59,190 --> 00:20:04,070
No. No, I won't do it.
It won't change anything.

325
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:06,200
I believe it will.

326
00:20:06,950 --> 00:20:09,910
There is more to

327
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,750
This time of year

328
00:20:12,830 --> 00:20:16,460
Than sleigh bells and holly

329
00:20:16,540 --> 00:20:19,840
Mistletoe and snow

330
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:22,800
Those things come and go

331
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:26,050
Much deeper than snow

332
00:20:26,140 --> 00:20:31,850
Stronger than the strongest Iove
we'll know

333
00:20:31,930 --> 00:20:34,730
We'll ever know

334
00:20:40,900 --> 00:20:45,200
As Iong as there's Christmas

335
00:20:45,280 --> 00:20:49,410
l truly believe

336
00:20:49,490 --> 00:20:53,710
That hope is the greatest

337
00:20:53,790 --> 00:20:58,210
Of the gifts we'II receive

338
00:20:58,290 --> 00:21:02,420
As Iong as there's Christmas

339
00:21:02,510 --> 00:21:06,550
We'll all be just fine

340
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:10,510
A star shines above us

341
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:14,850
Lighting your way and mine

342
00:21:17,020 --> 00:21:21,190
Just as Iong as there's Christmas
there wiII be Christmas pud

343
00:21:21,610 --> 00:21:22,610
Tons of turkey

344
00:21:22,690 --> 00:21:25,280
And cranberry sauce and mince pies
if we're good

345
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:29,490
-Lots of logs on the fire
-Lots of gifts on the tree

346
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:31,790
All wrapped up in red ribbons

347
00:21:31,870 --> 00:21:33,830
Wonder if there's one for me

348
00:21:33,910 --> 00:21:38,000
We're due for a party
Where on earth do we start

349
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:42,130
l may wear my tiara
you bought me in Montmartre

350
00:21:42,210 --> 00:21:44,380
All the silver will sparkle

351
00:21:44,470 --> 00:21:46,470
And the china will gleam

352
00:21:46,550 --> 00:21:50,800
And we'll be as shiny
as a brand-new centime

353
00:21:50,890 --> 00:21:54,930
-After dinner we'll play games
-Till the morning breaks through

354
00:21:55,020 --> 00:21:56,810
Then we'll meet in the garden

355
00:21:56,890 --> 00:21:59,770
-This is what we shall do
-We will build

356
00:21:59,860 --> 00:22:03,320
We will build a snowman
that'll reach to the sky

357
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:07,860
lt will stay up until July

358
00:22:17,790 --> 00:22:20,250
What are you doing? Stop, stop, stop.

359
00:22:20,330 --> 00:22:24,130
Put me down. Put me down.
This is ridiculous.

360
00:22:24,210 --> 00:22:27,380
Everyone knows that
the lights go on first.

361
00:22:29,590 --> 00:22:32,800
I don't want to go
all the way up there on the top.

362
00:22:32,890 --> 00:22:36,730
As Iong as there's Christmas

363
00:22:36,810 --> 00:22:40,690
l truly believe

364
00:22:40,770 --> 00:22:44,820
That hope is the greatest

365
00:22:44,900 --> 00:22:48,780
Of the gifts we'II receive

366
00:22:48,860 --> 00:22:52,820
As Iong as there's Christmas

367
00:22:52,910 --> 00:22:56,830
We'll all be just fine

368
00:22:56,910 --> 00:23:03,630
There'II aIways be Christmas

369
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:09,010
So there aIways wiII be a time

370
00:23:09,090 --> 00:23:11,180
When the world

371
00:23:11,260 --> 00:23:14,390
ls filled with peace

372
00:23:14,470 --> 00:23:20,100
And warmth

373
00:23:21,850 --> 00:23:24,480
We're gonna have
the greatest Christmas ever.

374
00:23:24,570 --> 00:23:26,980
Oh, I hope so, Chip.

375
00:23:29,650 --> 00:23:32,110
You on the left,
you on the right, follow me.

376
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:34,450
-There is decorating to be done.

377
00:23:34,530 --> 00:23:39,000
Yes, yes, yes, yes. But keep in mind,
the master mustn't find out.

378
00:23:40,660 --> 00:23:43,290
Ooh, yes.

379
00:23:44,210 --> 00:23:48,170
Christmas?
She's planning Christmas?

380
00:23:48,420 --> 00:23:51,930
Yes. Awful, isn't it?

381
00:24:00,270 --> 00:24:02,940
Perhaps she doesn't know
how I feel about Christmas.

382
00:24:03,020 --> 00:24:05,060
-But she does know.
-Hmm?

383
00:24:05,150 --> 00:24:08,980
She just doesn't care like I do.

384
00:24:11,150 --> 00:24:13,700
She's actually trying to bring
Christmas back to the castle.

385
00:24:13,780 --> 00:24:18,160
And you know how much
we despise Christmas.

386
00:24:18,240 --> 00:24:20,700
The day my life ended.

387
00:24:23,040 --> 00:24:26,960
-Bring me my presents!
-Your Highness,

388
00:24:27,040 --> 00:24:30,920
please accept this humble gift
as a token of our appreciation.

389
00:24:31,010 --> 00:24:33,260
I know I speak for everyone when...

390
00:24:33,340 --> 00:24:35,470
Ah, just give it to me!

391
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:40,470
A storybook? You call this a present?

392
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:43,600
I hope you have something
better for me, Forte.

393
00:24:43,690 --> 00:24:46,690
Yes, sir. Of course, master.

394
00:24:51,530 --> 00:24:53,190
What is that?

395
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:57,320
Um, a small piece in your honor, master.

396
00:24:57,660 --> 00:25:01,290
Ew! I hate it.
Forte, that stuff is gloomy.

397
00:25:04,750 --> 00:25:07,250
Who disturbs my Christmas?

398
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:11,300
Please, take this rose

399
00:25:11,380 --> 00:25:15,720
in exchange for shelter
from the bitter cold.

400
00:25:16,760 --> 00:25:19,180
I don't need a rose.

401
00:25:19,260 --> 00:25:21,180
Go away, you wretched old hag!

402
00:25:24,270 --> 00:25:28,860
You have been deceived
by your own cold heart.

403
00:25:28,940 --> 00:25:32,400
A curse upon your house
and all within it.

404
00:25:33,610 --> 00:25:37,610
Until you have found one
to love you as you are,

405
00:25:37,700 --> 00:25:41,780
you shall remain forever a beast.

406
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:53,760
But we've come so far since then.

407
00:25:53,840 --> 00:25:57,550
We've risen above the tragedy.

408
00:25:57,640 --> 00:26:00,220
Where is she?

409
00:26:00,300 --> 00:26:03,680
I believe she's gone to the boiler room,

410
00:26:03,770 --> 00:26:06,940
or so, a little birdie told me.

411
00:26:07,140 --> 00:26:09,810
Tweet, tweet, tweet.

412
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:16,240
Oh!

413
00:26:21,660 --> 00:26:22,830
Aah!

414
00:26:32,590 --> 00:26:34,500
Hey, hey, hey. Come on.
Get out of the way.

415
00:26:34,590 --> 00:26:36,970
-We're workin' here.

416
00:26:37,050 --> 00:26:40,550
-Excuse me.
-Let's go. Let's go.

417
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:43,680
All right, you guys.
Now, get back to work.

418
00:26:43,760 --> 00:26:46,310
The castle doesn't heat itself,
you know.

419
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:50,100
So, what can I do you for, lady?

420
00:26:50,190 --> 00:26:53,440
-I'm looking for a log.
-All right. Logs we got.

421
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:56,610
What do you want? Hard wood?
Soft wood? We got it all.

422
00:26:56,690 --> 00:26:58,740
We got birch, maple, pine, oak...

423
00:26:58,820 --> 00:27:01,240
- Concrete.

424
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:04,030
-My head. Don't worry. It'll pass.

425
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:06,290
So, make up your mind already.

426
00:27:06,370 --> 00:27:09,120
Is it all right if I just browse?

427
00:27:09,210 --> 00:27:12,500
Suit yourself. Take your time.
Me, I got work to do.

428
00:27:13,710 --> 00:27:14,750
Huh.

429
00:27:15,880 --> 00:27:16,880
Hmm.

430
00:27:28,810 --> 00:27:30,440
-Whew.

431
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:33,020
Hey, what am I payin' you for,
being boring?

432
00:27:33,110 --> 00:27:36,230
Do that on your own time.
Get out of here!

433
00:27:37,990 --> 00:27:39,360
Yes.

434
00:27:40,740 --> 00:27:42,070
Oh!

435
00:27:50,830 --> 00:27:52,750
What are you hiding?

436
00:28:00,420 --> 00:28:02,720
It's a Yule log.

437
00:28:02,930 --> 00:28:04,010
Huh?

438
00:28:04,090 --> 00:28:05,760
A... A Yule log.

439
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:09,060
It's a wonderful tradition.

440
00:28:09,140 --> 00:28:12,440
One log is chosen and everyone
in the house touches it

441
00:28:12,520 --> 00:28:14,690
and makes a Christmas wish.

442
00:28:15,110 --> 00:28:17,440
Mmm, wishes are stupid.

443
00:28:19,320 --> 00:28:22,530
You made a Christmas wish last year.

444
00:28:22,610 --> 00:28:26,370
Is this what you wished for?

445
00:28:29,790 --> 00:28:31,000
No.

446
00:28:33,170 --> 00:28:35,290
But I will keep wishing.

447
00:28:35,710 --> 00:28:37,670
And when the log is burned
on Christmas morning...

448
00:28:37,750 --> 00:28:39,630
There will be no Christmas.

449
00:28:39,710 --> 00:28:44,380
-But...
-No! I am the master here.

450
00:28:44,470 --> 00:28:47,180
How can you be so selfish?

451
00:28:47,260 --> 00:28:50,350
You cannot possibly understand.

452
00:28:50,430 --> 00:28:53,680
You have no idea
what it's like to lose everything,

453
00:28:53,770 --> 00:28:55,940
to be trapped in your own castle,

454
00:28:56,020 --> 00:28:58,310
to be a... A... A...

455
00:28:58,400 --> 00:28:59,820
Prisoner?

456
00:29:01,610 --> 00:29:05,070
The only one holding us prisoner here
is you.

457
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:07,240
Well, I'm not giving up.

458
00:29:12,500 --> 00:29:14,160
Prisoner.

459
00:29:33,680 --> 00:29:36,440
Hiya, Belle.
You should see the ballroom.

460
00:29:36,520 --> 00:29:39,110
It's all decorated and pretty
and there's garlands everywhere.

461
00:29:39,190 --> 00:29:41,110
I think the master's gonna
be really excited

462
00:29:41,190 --> 00:29:43,280
when he finds out about Christmas.

463
00:29:43,360 --> 00:29:46,450
Well, he... He already knows.

464
00:29:46,530 --> 00:29:49,280
Really? Was he excited?

465
00:29:49,370 --> 00:29:52,540
Actually, Chip, he's forbidden it.

466
00:29:53,580 --> 00:29:57,370
But I thought
he couldn't forbid Christmas.

467
00:29:58,710 --> 00:30:01,460
You know, Chip, he can't.

468
00:30:01,550 --> 00:30:03,880
We'll have Christmas
with or without him.

469
00:30:03,960 --> 00:30:09,090
Hurray! Can we get a tree now, Belle?
It's the only thing we're missing.

470
00:30:09,180 --> 00:30:12,140
All right, then. Let's go get a tree.

471
00:30:12,640 --> 00:30:14,220
But first...

472
00:30:15,230 --> 00:30:16,390
Shh.

473
00:30:26,860 --> 00:30:30,320
Psst, Belle.
The master. Hurry.

474
00:30:51,510 --> 00:30:53,430
What about this one?

475
00:30:56,310 --> 00:30:57,680
Mmm...

476
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:01,940
Mmm.

477
00:31:03,110 --> 00:31:06,860
Nah, too skinny. Come on.

478
00:31:19,500 --> 00:31:20,920
Ooo la-la.

479
00:31:22,380 --> 00:31:26,340
-Ohh, Lumiere.
-She's beautiful, no?

480
00:31:26,420 --> 00:31:29,050
Yes, and I'm hideous.

481
00:31:29,130 --> 00:31:31,430
Not to mention
ill-tempered.

482
00:31:31,510 --> 00:31:34,720
What? What is that?

483
00:31:34,810 --> 00:31:37,680
Ooh, it looks like a Christmas present.

484
00:31:45,820 --> 00:31:48,320
Oh-ho-ho. It's for you, master.

485
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:50,990
It's from a girl.

486
00:31:53,160 --> 00:31:56,330
-Mrs. Potts?
-No. From Belle.

487
00:31:58,000 --> 00:31:59,330
Belle?

488
00:32:02,790 --> 00:32:05,250
Uh-uh-uh. Master, you can't open it.

489
00:32:05,340 --> 00:32:07,710
Well, why not? It's for me, isn't it?

490
00:32:07,800 --> 00:32:10,090
Because it's not yet Christmas.

491
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:16,390
Master, we all understand
how you feel about Christmas.

492
00:32:16,470 --> 00:32:21,270
But when a woman gives a man a gift,
she's saying, "I care about you."

493
00:32:21,390 --> 00:32:22,560
Hmm.

494
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:24,600
But I don't have a gift for her.

495
00:32:24,690 --> 00:32:26,440
It is not too late.

496
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:32,150
Well, I guess I could
get her a little something.

497
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:39,450
Forte, stop the noise!

498
00:32:39,540 --> 00:32:42,200
Noise? Noise?

499
00:32:42,750 --> 00:32:44,620
This is my masterpiece.

500
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:47,460
Master.

501
00:32:48,590 --> 00:32:50,630
I... I want you to compose a song.

502
00:32:50,710 --> 00:32:54,050
-It's a present for Belle.
-What? Belle?

503
00:32:55,220 --> 00:32:57,850
And make it happy!

504
00:32:57,930 --> 00:33:01,890
Oh, but happiness is so depressing.

505
00:33:02,520 --> 00:33:05,650
What's next? Love songs?

506
00:33:07,520 --> 00:33:09,730
Wedding marches?

507
00:33:11,650 --> 00:33:15,150
It's all that girl's fault.

508
00:33:17,530 --> 00:33:19,330
What about this one?

509
00:33:19,410 --> 00:33:24,290
-Hmm, too wiggly.
-Too wiggly.

510
00:33:24,370 --> 00:33:25,500
Fife!

511
00:33:28,460 --> 00:33:29,630
Pay attention.

512
00:33:29,710 --> 00:33:34,420
I need you to pace when I think.
The girl is evil, I tell you.

513
00:33:34,510 --> 00:33:36,630
She pulls him from my grasp.

514
00:33:36,720 --> 00:33:39,350
She fills his head with dreams of love

515
00:33:39,430 --> 00:33:42,140
and hope and Christmas!

516
00:33:42,220 --> 00:33:45,810
Well, what you gonna do?
You can't stop Christmas.

517
00:33:45,890 --> 00:33:50,900
No, but I can stop the girl.

518
00:33:54,900 --> 00:33:58,450
Chip, this is the last one.

519
00:33:58,530 --> 00:34:02,410
That's not it. That's just a weed
wishing it was a tree.

520
00:34:02,490 --> 00:34:05,870
Chip, we've looked
at every tree on the grounds.

521
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:08,710
But it's more this way than that.

522
00:34:08,790 --> 00:34:10,670
It will have to do.

523
00:34:13,590 --> 00:34:16,470
-What a headache I have.
-I'm sorry.

524
00:34:16,550 --> 00:34:18,340
I... I'll get a saw.

525
00:34:18,430 --> 00:34:21,470
No, that's fine.
I don't want I should put you out.

526
00:34:21,560 --> 00:34:23,260
Oh, all right.

527
00:34:24,980 --> 00:34:28,560
Do you have some oil?
I just thought a little massage...

528
00:34:28,650 --> 00:34:31,560
But if it's no, it's no. Go on.
What are you waiting for?

529
00:34:31,650 --> 00:34:33,770
Knock yourself out.

530
00:34:34,740 --> 00:34:36,940
You never get headaches, I guess.
Lucky you.

531
00:34:37,030 --> 00:34:40,320
-Really, I can get a saw.
-Who wants a saw?

532
00:34:40,410 --> 00:34:43,740
I said go ahead with the whacking
and the hitting. Who's stopping you?

533
00:34:43,830 --> 00:34:45,620
-Shh.

534
00:34:45,700 --> 00:34:47,500
What is that?

535
00:34:54,340 --> 00:34:55,500
Ohh.

536
00:34:56,420 --> 00:34:58,470
It's beautiful.

537
00:35:02,180 --> 00:35:05,890
And now for a little Fife.

538
00:35:13,320 --> 00:35:15,020
Sultan, wait!

539
00:35:16,530 --> 00:35:20,780
Don't worry yourself about me.
I'll just sit here. Snow is fine.

540
00:35:21,240 --> 00:35:23,450
A little wet, but who's complaining?

541
00:35:23,740 --> 00:35:28,330
Yes, my dear. Come to me.

542
00:35:28,710 --> 00:35:31,370
Come here, boy. Come here.

543
00:35:40,010 --> 00:35:43,390
-Good doggy. Nice doggy.

544
00:35:44,550 --> 00:35:47,060
Sultan?
Back off, doggy.

545
00:35:48,230 --> 00:35:49,310
Oh.

546
00:35:49,890 --> 00:35:54,770
Hello?

547
00:35:54,860 --> 00:35:57,530
Well, maybe there's nobody here.

548
00:35:58,240 --> 00:36:01,030
Maybe we should go.

549
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:04,530
What's the matter, Sultan?

550
00:36:07,950 --> 00:36:12,080
Oh, hello. I don't believe we've met.
I... I'm Belle.

551
00:36:12,420 --> 00:36:15,250
-And you are?
-Fife.

552
00:36:15,590 --> 00:36:18,170
-Down, boy, down.

553
00:36:18,260 --> 00:36:20,800
We heard the most beautiful music.

554
00:36:21,260 --> 00:36:23,590
-Was it you?
-Me?

555
00:36:23,680 --> 00:36:27,010
You thought that was me?

556
00:36:30,930 --> 00:36:32,640
Mademoiselle, please.

557
00:36:33,810 --> 00:36:36,940
I am Maestro Forte,

558
00:36:37,020 --> 00:36:41,400
court composer
and your most humble servant.

559
00:36:41,490 --> 00:36:44,700
Pleased to meet you, Monsieur Forte.
I'm Belle.

560
00:36:44,780 --> 00:36:49,160
Yes. The entire castle is talking
about you, child.

561
00:36:49,240 --> 00:36:54,040
They say you're planning
a Christmas gala. Marvelous idea.

562
00:36:54,120 --> 00:36:59,300
The very thing to shatter
the master's dark and gloomy past.

563
00:36:59,380 --> 00:37:03,590
But you must make this
the grandest celebration ever.

564
00:37:03,680 --> 00:37:05,090
-Have you gifts?
-Yep.

565
00:37:05,180 --> 00:37:06,180
-Food?
-Yep.

566
00:37:06,260 --> 00:37:08,390
-Garlands, ribbons, wreaths?
-Check.

567
00:37:08,470 --> 00:37:10,640
Spangles and "fandangles"?

568
00:37:10,720 --> 00:37:13,560
The trinkets, the trimmings,
the trappings?

569
00:37:13,640 --> 00:37:17,230
-Yep, we got 'em all.
-A tree?

570
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:21,780
See, Belle? I told you.

571
00:37:21,860 --> 00:37:23,490
Well, we found one.

572
00:37:23,570 --> 00:37:26,740
But it was on the piddlin' side of puny.

573
00:37:28,530 --> 00:37:31,910
But did you look in the Black Forest?

574
00:37:32,450 --> 00:37:34,910
There you will find a tree

575
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:38,290
better than any you can dream of.

576
00:37:38,380 --> 00:37:40,840
Better? We gotta go, Belle!

577
00:37:42,670 --> 00:37:45,380
-We gotta!
-Chip, we can't.

578
00:37:46,220 --> 00:37:50,100
I... I promised your master
I wouldn't leave the castle grounds.

579
00:37:50,180 --> 00:37:51,350
I gave my word.

580
00:37:51,430 --> 00:37:55,180
Chin up, son.
There's a profound lesson here.

581
00:37:55,890 --> 00:38:01,690
Keeping your word is much more
important than bringing joy to another.

582
00:38:01,780 --> 00:38:03,900
You're twisting what I said.

583
00:38:03,990 --> 00:38:06,950
Not at all. I agree with you.

584
00:38:07,030 --> 00:38:11,160
Look after yourself.
Let the master do the same.

585
00:38:11,240 --> 00:38:13,120
Never mind that the tree

586
00:38:13,200 --> 00:38:17,500
was always his favorite part
of Christmas.

587
00:38:17,580 --> 00:38:21,380
Please, Belle? Please?

588
00:38:22,880 --> 00:38:24,800
It looks dangerous.

589
00:38:24,880 --> 00:38:28,970
Mademoiselle,
you are in more danger

590
00:38:29,050 --> 00:38:32,470
in this very room, I assure you.

591
00:38:33,890 --> 00:38:34,930
All right.

592
00:38:35,020 --> 00:38:36,810
-Yes!
-We'll take Phillippe.

593
00:38:36,890 --> 00:38:38,980
If we hurry, we can be back by nightfall.

594
00:38:39,060 --> 00:38:42,560
-Hurray!
-Au revoir, Monsieur Forte.

595
00:38:43,070 --> 00:38:45,860
You'll keep my secret, won't you?

596
00:38:46,570 --> 00:38:48,820
Of course, mademoiselle.

597
00:38:48,910 --> 00:38:52,280
The master will remain
completely in the dark.

598
00:38:52,370 --> 00:38:54,160
Au revoir, Fife.

599
00:38:56,540 --> 00:38:59,500
Fife! I want you to follow her.

600
00:38:59,830 --> 00:39:03,670
Make sure they don't come back.

601
00:39:03,750 --> 00:39:07,130
Oh, yeah, but, Maestro, she's so nice.

602
00:39:07,220 --> 00:39:09,680
When you're finished fawning, Fife,

603
00:39:09,760 --> 00:39:14,640
perhaps you can recommend
someone else to play your solo.

604
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:17,100
No! I'm going. I'm going.

605
00:39:27,740 --> 00:39:31,780
-Cogsworth!
-Oh, dear. Yes. Coming. Coming.

606
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:34,660
Cogsworth!

607
00:39:34,740 --> 00:39:39,000
Running, running. Almost there.
You bellowed, sir?

608
00:39:39,080 --> 00:39:42,080
Find Belle. I... Uh...

609
00:39:42,170 --> 00:39:46,380
Well, I...
She has to hear a song.

610
00:39:46,460 --> 00:39:49,130
Yes, sir. Right away, sir. Uh, yes.

611
00:39:49,630 --> 00:39:52,890
Splendid. Yes, well... Splendid.

612
00:39:52,970 --> 00:39:54,010
Ho-ho-ho-ho-ho-ho.

613
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:58,020
Belle. Belle?

614
00:39:58,100 --> 00:40:00,270
Where is she? Belle?

615
00:40:01,350 --> 00:40:03,400
Careful, careful.

616
00:40:03,480 --> 00:40:06,570
Too fast! Get out of the way! Stop!

617
00:40:07,280 --> 00:40:08,280
Huh!

618
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:09,650
Amateurs.

619
00:40:10,110 --> 00:40:14,200
Belle? Here... Excuse me. Hello?

620
00:40:14,280 --> 00:40:17,620
Has anyone seen Belle?
I can't find her anywhere.

621
00:40:17,700 --> 00:40:19,830
And the master is demanding
to see her now.

622
00:40:19,910 --> 00:40:22,410
-He's got a song he wants her to hear.
-Ho-ho.

623
00:40:23,710 --> 00:40:28,670
Last I saw of her, she was going
with Chip to look for a Christmas tree.

624
00:40:30,590 --> 00:40:33,340
Right. We must conduct
a search of the grounds.

625
00:40:33,430 --> 00:40:35,180
-Lumiere, you're with me.
-Cogsworth!

626
00:40:36,350 --> 00:40:38,680
I'm waiting!

627
00:40:38,770 --> 00:40:41,890
Oh, dear. Running, running, running.
I'm almost there, sir.

628
00:40:42,850 --> 00:40:45,480
Mrs. Potts, stall the master.
All right, Lumiere, we're...

629
00:40:45,560 --> 00:40:48,230
Lumiere? Wait, I'm leading.

630
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:50,480
Me first, you second.

631
00:40:52,490 --> 00:40:56,370
Belle! Belle! Where is she?

632
00:40:56,450 --> 00:40:59,120
Belle? Belle?

633
00:40:59,200 --> 00:41:00,620
Belle, where are you?

634
00:41:00,700 --> 00:41:02,960
Lumiere, wait.

635
00:41:07,130 --> 00:41:09,040
Hmm?

636
00:41:10,170 --> 00:41:12,380
The Black Forest!

637
00:41:13,130 --> 00:41:15,090
Come along. Hurry now!

638
00:41:16,090 --> 00:41:17,470
Oh, no.

639
00:41:17,550 --> 00:41:19,470
This is catastrophic!

640
00:41:20,390 --> 00:41:22,770
Cogsworth, quit dawdling.

641
00:41:22,850 --> 00:41:24,980
I'm not dawdling. I'm waddling.

642
00:41:25,060 --> 00:41:29,730
Well, don't waddle then.
We're in a hurry, you lazy old clock.

643
00:41:34,360 --> 00:41:39,910
Hmm? Hmm?

644
00:41:45,750 --> 00:41:48,420
Why am I still waiting?

645
00:41:48,920 --> 00:41:52,210
-Mrs. Potts!
-Coming, sir! Coming!

646
00:41:52,670 --> 00:41:54,630
What a brisk day!

647
00:41:54,720 --> 00:41:58,300
Why, you look positively chilled
to the bone.

648
00:41:58,890 --> 00:42:00,510
Where's Belle?

649
00:42:00,600 --> 00:42:04,520
How about a nice cup of tea, sir?
Just a spot.

650
00:42:04,890 --> 00:42:06,060
Hmm.

651
00:42:07,100 --> 00:42:09,610
Forte, play Belle's song!

652
00:42:12,530 --> 00:42:13,940
Hot.

653
00:42:15,490 --> 00:42:17,280
You're not singing!

654
00:42:19,320 --> 00:42:24,450
Deck the halls
with boughs of holly

655
00:42:24,540 --> 00:42:28,290
Fa-la-la-la-la
La-la-la-la

656
00:42:28,370 --> 00:42:29,670
Louder!

657
00:42:30,500 --> 00:42:32,500
'Tis the season

658
00:42:32,590 --> 00:42:35,880
A bit more tea, sir?
Good for the heart, you know.

659
00:42:35,970 --> 00:42:37,050
No, thank you.

660
00:42:37,130 --> 00:42:39,130
-Just a spot?
-No more.

661
00:42:39,220 --> 00:42:42,300
-Well, there's always room for tea, love.
-I said, "No more."

662
00:42:42,390 --> 00:42:44,720
-Oh, dearie me!
-Mrs. Potts,

663
00:42:44,810 --> 00:42:47,810
are you trying to distract me?

664
00:42:47,890 --> 00:42:50,980
Goodness, no, sir.

665
00:42:51,060 --> 00:42:53,900
Heavens. Is that a yellow-bellied,
double-breasted sapsucker?

666
00:42:53,980 --> 00:42:57,150
-Rare this time of year.
-Enough! Where's Cogsworth?

667
00:42:57,240 --> 00:42:59,360
-Where's Belle?
-Belle?

668
00:42:59,450 --> 00:43:03,080
We can't find her, sir.

669
00:43:03,160 --> 00:43:04,580
What?

670
00:43:04,660 --> 00:43:06,040
Leave me!

671
00:43:08,710 --> 00:43:10,710
Show me the girl.

672
00:43:16,340 --> 00:43:18,720
-I will bring her back!
-No!

673
00:43:18,930 --> 00:43:21,180
Um, she's abandoned you.

674
00:43:21,260 --> 00:43:24,260
-Listen to your old friend, won't you?

675
00:43:24,350 --> 00:43:27,560
Have I ever steered you wrong?
Led you astray?

676
00:43:27,640 --> 00:43:30,480
No. But the girl...

677
00:43:31,020 --> 00:43:35,190
The quickest way
to break your heart

678
00:43:35,280 --> 00:43:38,940
Make you depressed and ill

679
00:43:39,030 --> 00:43:43,160
ls to get tangled up inside

680
00:43:43,240 --> 00:43:46,990
The side effects could kill

681
00:43:47,080 --> 00:43:51,160
All passion is a waste of time

682
00:43:51,250 --> 00:43:53,880
A deadly game pour vous

683
00:43:55,380 --> 00:43:59,340
l am your friend
Your cher ami

684
00:43:59,420 --> 00:44:04,050
l wouldn't lie to you

685
00:44:05,180 --> 00:44:08,520
lf you must love someone
may l suggest

686
00:44:08,600 --> 00:44:11,890
You love yourself
Just think it through

687
00:44:11,980 --> 00:44:15,400
You'll never leave
and you will find you'll get more rest

688
00:44:15,480 --> 00:44:18,820
You'll always feel
as good as new

689
00:44:18,900 --> 00:44:22,030
Your freedom is the most
important thing, my friend

690
00:44:22,110 --> 00:44:25,410
You must be strong
You mustn't bend

691
00:44:25,490 --> 00:44:27,490
Don't talk for hours
Don't send flowers

692
00:44:27,580 --> 00:44:29,580
Don't write poems
Don't sing songs and dance

693
00:44:29,660 --> 00:44:32,410
Beneath the stars
that shine above

694
00:44:32,500 --> 00:44:35,420
Don't fall in love

695
00:44:36,000 --> 00:44:39,300
-Oh, don't do it.

696
00:44:39,920 --> 00:44:40,960
Oh!

697
00:44:41,050 --> 00:44:45,260
As soon as your heart
rules your head

698
00:44:45,350 --> 00:44:48,850
Your life is not your own

699
00:44:48,930 --> 00:44:52,810
lt's hell when someone's always there

700
00:44:52,890 --> 00:44:56,810
lt's bliss to be alone

701
00:44:56,900 --> 00:45:00,820
And love of any kind is bad

702
00:45:00,900 --> 00:45:04,400
A dog, a child, a cat

703
00:45:04,490 --> 00:45:08,990
They take up so much precious time

704
00:45:09,080 --> 00:45:13,540
Now, where's the sense in that

705
00:45:15,540 --> 00:45:18,960
Love takes the wildest heart
and makes it tame

706
00:45:19,050 --> 00:45:22,300
lf you're turned on
then just turn off

707
00:45:22,380 --> 00:45:25,880
Emotions are a thing
all great men overcame

708
00:45:25,970 --> 00:45:29,140
Please, don't make
this grande catastrophe

709
00:45:29,220 --> 00:45:32,640
Don't get attached
to anyone or anything

710
00:45:32,730 --> 00:45:36,020
There's nothing worse
than things that cling

711
00:45:36,100 --> 00:45:37,810
You'll go to pot
You'll turn to drink

712
00:45:37,900 --> 00:45:39,520
You'll never rest
You'll end up mad

713
00:45:39,610 --> 00:45:43,280
And looking like
some poor demented dove

714
00:45:43,360 --> 00:45:48,910
Don't fall in love

715
00:45:48,990 --> 00:45:52,160
Don't fall in love!

716
00:45:56,540 --> 00:45:59,330
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

717
00:45:59,420 --> 00:46:02,590
They cannot mix bells with holly.

718
00:46:02,670 --> 00:46:06,300
Still, I have to admit,
not bad for amateurs.

719
00:46:22,570 --> 00:46:25,360
I knew this was hopeless.

720
00:46:56,890 --> 00:46:59,230
There. That's it! That's it!

721
00:47:02,230 --> 00:47:04,770
Oh, Chip, it's perfect.

722
00:47:11,620 --> 00:47:15,990
-Do you see her?
-Not yet. Now, come along. Hurry!

723
00:47:19,500 --> 00:47:22,330
-You go on. I'll never make it.

724
00:47:25,760 --> 00:47:27,300
Save yourself.

725
00:47:28,760 --> 00:47:31,470
Ah, it will be summer
before we reach them.

726
00:47:31,550 --> 00:47:33,300
What the... Whoa!

727
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:35,640
Oh, dear!

728
00:47:39,020 --> 00:47:41,600
Faster! Faster!

729
00:47:41,690 --> 00:47:43,980
I think we finally found a use for you.

730
00:47:44,070 --> 00:47:46,690
Clock boarding! No, snow clocking!

731
00:47:47,530 --> 00:47:48,990
Whatever!

732
00:47:50,610 --> 00:47:52,490
Whoo!

733
00:47:55,120 --> 00:47:57,450
Whoa!

734
00:47:59,960 --> 00:48:04,040
-It's the best tree ever!
-Chip, you're right.

735
00:48:04,130 --> 00:48:08,300
Merry Christmas!
And a happy Hanukkah!

736
00:48:08,970 --> 00:48:12,090
We better hurry.
It's getting very stormy.

737
00:48:15,140 --> 00:48:17,220
Again with the chopping.

738
00:48:17,970 --> 00:48:21,600
Oh, I gotta do something.
Forte's counting on me.

739
00:48:27,650 --> 00:48:30,110
Timber!

740
00:48:35,620 --> 00:48:36,660
Phew!

741
00:48:38,160 --> 00:48:40,160
Take it away, Phillippe!

742
00:48:43,040 --> 00:48:44,170
Whoo!

743
00:48:45,460 --> 00:48:46,540
Whoa!

744
00:48:52,260 --> 00:48:53,590
Oh, no!

745
00:49:00,310 --> 00:49:02,640
Aah! Aah! Aaah!

746
00:49:06,860 --> 00:49:08,110
Fife?

747
00:49:08,190 --> 00:49:10,150
Uh, hi, Belle.

748
00:49:10,820 --> 00:49:12,360
Nice tree.

749
00:49:12,900 --> 00:49:14,780
What are you doing way out here?

750
00:49:14,860 --> 00:49:17,780
Uh, nothin'. I just was walkin'.

751
00:49:17,870 --> 00:49:21,080
I mean, I love the bitter cold. I mean...
Hee, hee!

752
00:49:27,210 --> 00:49:28,750
Phillippe!

753
00:49:33,260 --> 00:49:34,720
Oh, no!

754
00:49:39,560 --> 00:49:41,640
The tree, Belle!
We're gonna lose the tree!

755
00:49:41,720 --> 00:49:43,270
Whoa!

756
00:49:44,100 --> 00:49:46,100
Chip! Oh!

757
00:49:47,190 --> 00:49:48,650
Where is he?

758
00:49:48,730 --> 00:49:51,070
Whoa! Whoa!

759
00:50:09,250 --> 00:50:10,420
Oh!

760
00:50:16,840 --> 00:50:20,680
-Hold on, chérie. I will save you!
-Oh, dear!

761
00:50:21,260 --> 00:50:24,770
Oh, no. Oh, gosh. Oh, no.
Oh, gosh. Oh, no. Oh, gosh.

762
00:50:25,180 --> 00:50:26,520
Oh, no!

763
00:50:37,610 --> 00:50:42,080
-Oh, Chip, thank goodness you're safe.
-I wasn't scared.

764
00:50:46,210 --> 00:50:47,830
Oh, no! No!

765
00:51:13,270 --> 00:51:14,650
Belle!

766
00:51:26,160 --> 00:51:29,080
Oh, no, what have I done?

767
00:51:30,000 --> 00:51:31,750
It's all my fault.

768
00:51:31,830 --> 00:51:37,260
We all share some blame, mon ami,
for daring to hope for a Christmas.

769
00:51:59,360 --> 00:52:01,820
You said you'd never leave.

770
00:52:06,120 --> 00:52:08,450
I wasn't trying to leave.

771
00:52:10,290 --> 00:52:13,000
I just wanted to make you happy.

772
00:52:15,460 --> 00:52:18,590
You broke your word.

773
00:52:18,670 --> 00:52:24,140
And for that, you will rot
in this dungeon forever.

774
00:52:26,010 --> 00:52:30,560
I should have known
you'd never be anything but a beast.

775
00:52:36,230 --> 00:52:38,070
Midnight.

776
00:52:38,150 --> 00:52:40,610
Merry Christmas, Cogsworth.

777
00:52:41,030 --> 00:52:42,990
If only it were.

778
00:52:45,570 --> 00:52:51,160
Oh, my dear old friend,
I told you not to feel for her.

779
00:52:51,790 --> 00:52:56,420
Things were so much simpler
before she came along,

780
00:52:56,500 --> 00:53:00,510
before we dared to hope.

781
00:53:01,170 --> 00:53:05,390
Oh, I thought she was the one.

